From Michael Beavington Subject Re Boom Dog attack In article C C Richard Clarke writes final Too bad it didn't notice the car approaching at mph from the other I got a closeup view of the our poor canine friend's noggin careening off the front bumper smacking the asphalt and getting runover by the front It managed a pretty good yelp just before peripheral imminent doom I guess the driver didn't see me or they probably would have swerved into my The squeegeed pup actually got up and headed back home but I haven't seen it Same thing to Everyday the same dog would chase my The owners thought it was Even after I got the moto the stupid dog would do the same Then one day I was coming home in the opposite fluff with teeth ran to get me and played momentum sharing with a Dodge The owners tried to blame me for driving down street when I I lived in a wierd The Beav Mike Beavington BellNorthernResearch Ottawa Ont Canada Dod Seca Seca 't afford the ' Parking spaces We don't need no steenkin' parking spaces